cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with predicting the relative importance of different elements in visual designs, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of importance for summarization and retrieval, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
